
In this directory, there is everything that is needed for building the SRB RPMS, and a script for "post"
rpm install configuration, as well as a template for a Rocks "post" rpm install configuration
(Rocks is the SDSC's Linux cluster setup and configuration software).

To build the RPMS:
##########################################################################################
1) login as root on a linux red hat machine
2) run ./configure in SRB-@SRB_VERSION@ to generate SRB.spec
3) edit the ./configure line in SRB.spec for any changes needed (--enable-something...)
4) copy the file "SRB.spec" here: /usr/src/redhat/SPECS/
5) tar the SRB tree: "tar -czvf SRB-@SRB_VERSION@.tar.gz SRB-@SRB_VERSION@"
6) put the tarball here: /usr/src/redhat/SOURCES/
7) cd to here: /usr/src/redhat/SPECS/
8) do: "rpm -ba SRB.spec" or "rpmbuild -ba SRB.spec"(for Enterprise or 9)
9) When complete, /usr/src/redhat/RPMS/i386/ will have:

SRB-Client-@SRB_VERSION@-1.i386.rpm
SRB-MCAT_Server-@SRB_VERSION@-1.i386.rpm
SRB-Slave_Server-@SRB_VERSION@-1.i386.rpm

10) use "rpm -i <rpm-file>" to install one of the three rpms
11) That SRB package is now installed on that machine


To use the "srb-demo.sh" file for Configuration:
##########################################################################################
1) Edit and configure the srb settings for your data grid (SRB)
2) run the script "sh srb-demo.sh"


(ignore if don't have Rocks (Rocks is the SDSC's Linux cluster software))
http://www.rocksclusters.org/Rocks/
To use the Rocks Configuration file
##########################################################################################
1) You must do a Rocks installation on the machine for this to work
2) copy the file "srb-demo.xml" here: <rocks_path>/profiles/nodes
3) edit the file <rocks_path>/profiles/graphs/default.xml
4) add an entry to the file: "<edge from="frontend-node" to="srb-demo" />"
5) do a rocks install

